phase2.explanation:
The class opens a file but never closes it!

**What's happening:**
1. `file.open()` opens the file
2. No destructor to close it
3. The file handle stays open

**The fix:**
```cpp
class GoodFileHandler {
private:
    std::fstream file;

public:
    GoodFileHandler(const std::string& name) {
        file.open(name, std::ios::out);
        if (!file.is_open()) {
            throw std::runtime_error("Failed to open file");
        }
    }

    ~GoodFileHandler() {
        if (file.is_open()) {
            file.close();  // ← Close in destructor!
        }
    }
};
```

**PlusPlus-chan says:**
"RAII means: if you acquire a resource in the constructor, release it in the destructor. Always."

